<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Policeman Killed While Searching for Abducted Women </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 11 (Xinhua) -- A 31-year-old Chinese policeman
of Mongolia nationality was killed last night while searching for
kidnapped women in a village in north China's Inner Mongolia
Autonomous Region, the Ministry of Public Security disclosed today.
</P>
<P>
The policeman, Sainbair, and his two colleagues were
investigating in the village when Han Yonglai, a 32-year-old
farmer who bought an abducted woman from southwest China's Sichuan
Province, attacked him with a knife.
</P>
<P>
Sainbair died on the way to the hospital.
</P>
<P>
According to police sources, Sainbair is the first police
officer to be killed in the line of duty since the nationwide hunt
for traffickers of women and children kicked off on April 1 this
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
