<HEADLINE> U.N. Special Envoy Arrives in Ethiopia for Drought Information </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Catherine Bertini, special
envoy of U. N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan, arrived here on
Tuesday to gather information about the current drought situation
in Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
She was briefed by Ethiopia's Disaster Prevention and
Preparedness Commissioner (DPPC) Simeon Mechale Wednesday on how
the emergency relief assistance is being distributed to the famine
victims.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia had appealed earlier to the international community to
extend relief food to the drought affected people, Simeon said,
adding that over 836,000 tons of relief food is required, but only
half of the assistance has so far been obtained.
</P>
<P>
Responding to how Ethiopia could cope with the large quantity
of shipment of relief assistance as it only uses Djibouti port,
the commissioner said the ports of Sudan and Somalia could be used
as alternatives.
</P>
<P>
There would not be a problem in transport as there are enough
number of trucks that could be leased, he said.
</P>
<P>
According to the DPPC, Bertini and her entourage would inspect
one of the drought-hit areas, Gode, in Somali State during the
visit. 
</P>
