Philippine News Agency said.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed by President Joseph Estrada's special
emissary Roberto Aventajado and MILF chief Hashim Salamat in Camp
Abubakar, the rebel group's headquarters in Matanog, Maguindanao
Province.
</P>
<P>
Witnessing the signing were Edgardo Batenga, chairman of the
government peace panel, and Aleem Mimbantas, chairman of the MILF
peace panel.
</P>
<P>
"It is necessary to halt all hostilities in the project area in
order to ensure that the irrigation project is completed on time,"
Aventajado was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
When completed in 200l, the 1-billion-peso (25-million-U.S.
dollar)project will irrigate some 10,000 hectares of farmland.
</P>
<P>
Aventajado, also chairman of the Presidential Committee on
Flagship Programs and Projects, stressed that development is the
key to peace in Mindanao.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, President Estrada endorsed the MILF Economic
Development Committee's plan to develop Muslim Mindanao,
particularly those places within MILF camps.
</P>
<P>
The plan calls for the conversion of the MILF camps into
special economic zones.
</P>
<P>
"President Estrada fully supports the MILF plan because he
believes that once the projects are realized, they will contribute
to the national government's efforts in the peace-building
initiatives in Mindanao," said Aventajado. 
</P>
