<HEADLINE> Singapore Union Urges New Survival Kit for Workers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 12 (Xinhua) -- The ongoing 10th Triennial
Delegates Conference of Singapore's National Trades Union Congress
emphasized the need to develop a new survival kit for the country'
s workers and help them find their ways through uncharted
territory.
</P>
<P>
In his work report to the conference Wednesday, the congress'
Secretary-General Lim Boon Heng said there will be more job
changes, shorter job tenure and more churn for workers in the new
economy, which will make some revel in this new environment and
others "confused,perplexed, unsure and scared."
</P>
<P>
He said the union should spend the time it has developing a new
survival kit for workers whose welfare in the new economy depends
less on employers and whose primary concern will be to have jobs
and to have the skills for the jobs.
</P>
<P>
Lim said the elements of this survival kit will include union
membership, skills, life-long learning and employment assistance,
portable medical benefits and personal savings for unemployment
and emergency rations.
</P>
<P>
"The new survival kit for workers in the new economy must
recognize that we are responsible for our own employability and
earning capacity," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
"We are responsible for seizing opportunities provided by
employers and government to upgrade our skills," he added.
</P>
<P>
He also said the social safety net should be based on '
portability' and "saving as we work."
</P>
<P>
"We should save-as-we-earn for medical coverage, for old age
and for the risk of unemployment," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Some 1,000 delegates from various trade unions in the country
are attending the two-day conference starting Wednesday morning.
</P>
<P>
At the opening ceremony, Singapore's acting Prime Minister Lee
Hsien Loong delivered a long speech on a number of issues closely
related to workers' interests and representatives from some
international and overseas national unions, including Vice-
Chairman of All-China Federation of Trade Unions Xu Xicheng,
delivered messages of congratulation to the conference. 
</P>
</TEXT>
