<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian President Hails Relations with China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In a telegram to Chinese President Jiang Zemin on the occasion
of the 50th anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic
relations between Indonesia and China, Wahid said Indonesia
attaches great importance to the friendship and cooperation
between his country and China.
</P>
<P>
Since the resumption of the diplomatic relations between
Indonesia and China in 1990, "the bonds of friendship and
cooperation between our two countries have considerably
strengthened in a way that has benefited our two peoples," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian president said that the range of bilateral
cooperation has significantly expanded as China and Indonesia have
cooperated closely at both the international and regional levels.
</P>
<P>
"Although there are many challenges ahead of China and
Indonesia in this new century and new millennium, I am confident
that together we will be able to overcome them and attain our
respective development goals while contributing to the shaping of
a more just, more prosperous world," Wahid said.
</P>
<P>
In a telegram to Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji, Wahid said that
the establishment of diplomatic relations between Indonesia and
China in April 1950 was a watershed event in the history of the
relationship between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Since then the relationship between our two countries has had
its share of vicissitudes. "Nevertheless we were eventually able
to overcome all obstacles to the growth of our friendship and
cooperation," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Our two countries are now both fully committed to broadening
and strengthening their relationship. I am confident that our two
governments will persevere in their efforts to attain that
objective, which is also the clear desire of our people," he said.
</P>
<P>
On the occasion, Indonesian Foreign Minister Alwi Shihab also
sent a telegram to Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan, saying
that China and Indonesia are today contributing significantly to
the promotion of peace and stability so necessary for the social
and economic development of the countries in the region by working
together "closely and constantly" in the ASEAN dialogue process,
the ASEAN regional forum, APEC and the Asia-Europe Meeting.
</P>
