<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Russian President-elect Vladimir
Putin appointed Andrei Illarionov as his advisor, said Putin's
spokesman Alexei Gromov on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Illarionov, 38, who graduated from the Leningrad University in
1983, had previously worked for the university's department of
international economic relations and acted as a senior researcher
at the St. Petersburg Finance and Economics Institute.
</P>
