<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA -- Ugandan police have located several witnesses who
stayed at the Kanungu cult camp in the southwestern Uganda on the
eve of March 17 when over 500 cult members were burnt to death,
the New Vision daily reported on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
After a three-week investigation, the police found that several
taxi operators had ferried hundreds of people to Kanungu from
different parts of the east African country, the newspaper quoted
Terence Kinyera, chief of criminal investigation department of the
southwestern region, as saying. (Uganda-Cult)
</P>
