<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israeli Court Orders Eight More Lebanese Detainees Released </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Israel's Supreme Court Wednesday
ruled that eight of the 15 Lebanese detainees now held by Israel
should be freed immediately as Israel should not keep them as
bargaining chips for its missing soldiers.
</P>
<P>
These Lebanese hostages, who had been held in administrative
detention for years, would be transferred to Lebanon in the next
few days, court source said.
</P>
<P>
Israel uses these Lebanese detainees as bargaining cards for
information or return of missing Israeli servicemen, including Ron
Arad, an Israeli Air Force navigator who has been missing since 14
years ago.
</P>
<P>
Five Lebanese hostages were freed last December and two more
freed in January this year. Last week, another one was released by
Tel Aviv District Court on the basis of his deteriorating mental
health after long-time detention.
</P>
<P>
The seven other prisoners, including two most prominent figures
Sheik Abdel Karim Obeid and Mustafa Dirani, are still being held
without a trial. It is still not clear whether they will be freed
at a later date.
</P>
<P>
Zvi Rish, the lawyer representing these detainees, asserted that
although the seven prisoners did not appeal for their release
currently, the ruling by a nine-judge panel of the Supreme Court
should also let them go in the future.
</P>
<P>
Obeid, spiritual leader of Lebanese Hezbollah guerrillas, was
kidnapped from his home in south Lebanon in 1989, and Dirani,
security chief of the Lebanese resistance militia Amal, was
captured by Israeli agents in a special operation in 1994.
</P>
<P>
It was Dirani who held Arad after the Israeli navigator
parachuted from his hit Phantom fighter on Lebanese soils in
October 1986. Dirani reportedly traded Arad to either Lebanese
Hezbollah guerrillas or Iranian elements later.
</P>
<P>
In response to the court ruling, Israeli Chief of General Staff
Shaul Mofaz said the Israel Defense Forces have objected to the
release of Lebanese detainees due to its moral responsibility to
ensure the return of Arad and other captured Israeli soldiers.
</P>
<P>
Now, Mofaz said, the army would have to learn the details of the
closed-door decision reached by a 6-3 vote before taking any
actions.
</P>
<P>
He vowed to Arad's family that the defense establishment would
continue its efforts to get Arad back to his homeland.
</P>
<P>
Arad's mother Batia Arad condemned the court decision, saying
she felt betrayed by the court. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000412.0107 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Arrives in Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tel Aviv, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
arrived here Wednesday for a state visit to Israel at the
invitation of Israeli President Ezer Weizman. 
</P>
<P>
This is the first visit by a Chinese head of state to the
country. During his visit, Jiang is expected to exchange views with
Israeli leaders on major international and regional issues of
common concern.   Jiang and his wife Wang Yeping were greeted at
the airport by President Weizman and his wife, and Israeli
Ambassador to China Ora Namir.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador to Israel Wang Changyi and his wife as well
as representatives from the Chinese Embassy in Israel were also at
the airport to greet President Jiang.
</P>
<P>
In a written speech distributed at the airport, Jiang said that
his current visit is to further strengthen the mutual understanding
and friendship between the Chinese and Israeli peoples and promote
the development of the existing friendly cooperation between the
two countries. 
</P>
<P>
Extending warm greetings and good wishes to the Israeli people
on behalf of the Chinese people, Jiang said that the Sino-Israeli
bilateral cooperation has achieved remarkable progress in the
fields of politics, economy and culture since the two countries
established diplomatic ties in 1992. 
</P>
<P>
"It has been proved that strengthening Sino-Israeli friendly
cooperation is not only in the common interest of the two peoples,
but beneficial to the peace and development in the region and in
the world at large," he added.  
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that at the turn of the century, peace and
development have become the issues that the international community
is concerned with, and pursuing peace, stability and development
are the common aspiration of the people of all countries in the
world.
</P>
<P>
However, the Middle East problem which has lasted for over half
a century has not only brought about great sufferings to the people
in the region, but adversely affected the region's the peace and
development, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The Middle East peace process is at a crucial juncture at
present, and China would like to make unremitting efforts to push
forward the process, Jiang said.  
</P>
<P>
Jiang's entourage arriving on the same special plane include
Vice Premier Qian Qichen and his wife, State Councillor Wu Yi,
Director of the General Office of the Chinese Communist Party (CPC)
Central Committee Wang Gang, Minister in charge of the State
Development Planning Commission Zeng Peiyan, Director of the Policy
Research Office of CPC Central Committee Teng Wensheng, Vice
Foreign Minister Ji Peiding, Vice Director of the General Office of
the CPC Central Committee and Director of the Central Guards Bureau
You Xigui, Vice Minister of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation
Sun Guangxiang, Special Assistant Wang Huning and Director of
President Jiang's office Jia Ting'an.
</P>
<P>
Israel is the first leg of Jiang's five-nation tour of Asia,
Europe and Africa, which also includes stops in Palestine, Turkey,
Greece and South Africa.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang will also meet with Egyptian President Hosni
Mubarak in Alexandria City of Egypt. 
</P>
