<HEADLINE> Iranian Reformist Severely Injured in Traffic Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Rajabali Mazroui, one of the
leaders of Iran's major reformist party Islamic Iran Participation
Front (IIPF), was severely injured in a car accident on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Mazroui, also head of the Guilds Association of Journalists, was
hit by a car on the Rasht-Tehran road in Tehran province, the
Islamic Republic News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
A member of the Central Council of the IIPF, Mazroui is also an
elected member of the sixth Majlis (parliament), representing the
central province of Isfahan.
</P>
<P>
The IIPF led the reformists to a landslide victory in parliament
elections in February, dealing a severe blow to the powerful
conservatives.
</P>
<P>
Since the elections, there has been an air of tension between
political factions representing the reformists and conservatives.
</P>
<P>
Mazroui has been hospitalized in the intensive care unit of Dey
hospital in northern Tehran, the report said. The cause of the
accident is still not clear. 
</P>
