<HEADLINE> AmCham Chairman Supports Positive Vote on China's PNTR </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 12 (Xinhua) -- A positive vote for permanent
normal trade relations (PNTR) for China will allow American
businesses and workers to reap the full benefits of the historic U.
S.-China World Trade Organization accord reached last fall,
chairman of the American Chamber of Commerce in Hong Kong, Richard
Kahler, said today.
</P>
<P>
A positive vote will enhance U.S.-China trade relations,
advance China's economic development and spur China's orderly
integration into the global economy, Kahler told U.S. senators at
a congressional hearing, according to an AmCham new release faxed
here today.
</P>
<P>
The hearing, which was held by the Senate Commerce, Science and
Transportation Committee, was convened to consider the
implications of granting PNTR for China.
</P>
<P>
In his testimony, Kahler stated that China's accession to the
World Trade Organization will offer unparalleled opportunities for
American companies and workers while providing a stable legal
framework for trade and the impetus for furthering China's
economic reforms.  
