<HEADLINE> Britain Drawn at Home in Davis Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Britain have been drawn at home
against Ecuador in their relegation play-off in the Davis Cup
World Group.
</P>
<P>
Britain must win the tie to remain in the elite 16-nation World
Group next year.
</P>
<P>
The tie, the first under new captain Roger Taylor, will take
place after Wimbledon on the weekend of either 14-16 or 21-23 of
July.
</P>
<P>
Taylor said: "Sitting there in the front row while the draw was
being made there was a bit of a flutter when Equator came out and
we had to draw for choice of home or away but now I'm absolutely
delighted."
</P>
<P>
"We've been very lucky because there were no guaranteed home
ties and the odds were against us but now we have a tie at home on
grass after Wimbledon and with two of the best grass-court players
in the world with Greg Rusedski and Tim Henman. There will be a
lot of interest immediately after Wimbledon and we have to admit
we will now be favorites to go through," he said.
</P>
<P>
Following are the draws (Ties to take place 14-16 July 2000 and
21-23 July 2000; seeds in caps):
</P>
