<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fire Facilities Checked At Recreation Centers in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Beijing police has examined fire
fighting facilities in nearly 2,000 recreation centers over the
past 17 days to avoid further fire accidents like the one that
occurred in central China's Henan Province.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,500 policemen participated in the check which has
seen 37 centers close down. Police also issued some 362 notices,
warning of the dangers of possible fires.
</P>
<P>
Statistics showed that 5,395 cases of fire accidents occurred
in Beijing in 1999, killing 53 and injuring 92 in addition to some
31.65 million yuan (about 3.8 million U.S. dollars) worth
properties.
</P>
<P>
Seventy-four people were killed in a fire that broke out on
March 29 in a video parlor in Jiaozuo City of Henan Province.
</P>
<P>
The fire was caused by a heater in the video parlor, according
to local police. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
