<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shenzhen-Chicago Air Freight Route Inaugurated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, April 12 (Xinhua) -- China Southern Airlines today
inaugurated its first international air freight route from
Shenzhen in Guangdong Province to Chicago in the United States.
</P>
<P>
Three return flights a week will be available on the newly
launched route: at Shenzhen, the flights will take off every
Wednesday, Friday, and Sunday, while in Chicago, the flights will
be every Monday, Thursday, and Saturday, said corporate sources.
</P>
<P>
A Boeing 747-200 aircraft, capable of carrying 110 tons of
cargo, will be used for this air freight route.
</P>
<P>
Yan Zhiqing, president of China Southern Airlines, said at the
inauguration ceremony that the opening of the new route will play
a positive role in promoting economic and trade development in
south China, especially in Shenzhen and the Pearl River Delta, and
in improving relations between south China and the U.S.
</P>
<P>
With headquarters in Guangzhou, the provincial capital of
Guangdong, China Southern Airlines is one of the country's leading
air transport carriers, with a fleet of 101 Boeing and Airbus
planes operating 360 domestic and overseas air routes.
</P>
<P>
The airline carried 15.11 million passengers and shipped 390,
000 tons of cargo last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
