<HEADLINE> 2000 Year of IPO for Asian Internet Companies: Merrill Lynch </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Year 2000 will be the year of
initial public offerings (IPO) for Asian Internet companies, Matei
Mihalca, vice president of Merrill Lynch (Asia Pacific) Ltd. said
here today.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua, Mihalca, who also heads Merrill
Lynch's Asia-Pacific Internet Research, said Asia's economic
revival will buoy emerging Internet businesses across the region.
</P>
<P>
He estimates that 30 to 50 Asian Internet companies may issue
their IPOs on Nasdaq and other markets this year to raise an
aggregate of two billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Among these, he said five to 10 businesses will be from the
Chinese mainland.
</P>
<P>
Mihalca disclosed that three Chinese Internet companies, sohu,
sina and netease, are currently preparing for IPOs, and that
Merrill Lynch is leading one of them.
</P>
<P>
He added that the recent slide in the prices of Internet stocks
on the Nasdaq market will not lead to Merrill Lynch's reduced
investment in Chinese Internet enterprises, which is based on a
long-term strategy.  
</P>
</TEXT>
