<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Ensuring Supply of Quality Seedlings to Western China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 12 (Xinhua) -- The China State Forestry
Administration today issued a circular, urging localities to take
concrete steps to provide farmers with quality seedlings in the
country's drive to turn farmland to forest in western China.
</P>
<P>
A SFA official said that the supply of seedlings is adequate
on the whole, however, the prices of some varieties have surged
due to strong demand.
</P>
<P>
The circular asks localities in the region to strengthen market
management and firmly stop the illegal raising of seedling prices
while setting a top limit on these prices.
</P>
<P>
According to the circular, the seedlings needed in the planned
afforestation areas must be provided to farmers free of charge,
and state-allocated funds for this purpose will be withdrawn if
farmers do not get the seedlings.
</P>
<P>
Strong measures should be taken to eliminate sub-standard
seedlings, and if any institutions or individuals are found
selling such seedlings, they will be severely punished, the
circular stressed.
</P>
<P>
China has launched an ambitious drive to turn farmland to
forest in the west to improve the environment, and 340,000
hectares of farmland at the upper reaches of the Yangtze and
Yellow rivers will be turned to forest this year, while 430,00
hectares of wasteland and hills are afforested. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
