<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Magazine Publishes Article in Memory of Lenin (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 11 (Xinhua) -- "Seeking Truth", a theoretic
periodical of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of
China (CPC), will publish a signed article in its April 17 edition
in memory of the 130th anniversary of the birth of Vladimir Ilyich
Lenin (1870-1924), leader of the Bolshevik Revolution and founder
of the former Soviet Union.
</P>
<P>
The article, written by Li Zhongjie, a professor with the Party
School of the Central Committee of the CPC, urges people to learn
from Lenin's though and spirit in a scientific manner.
</P>
<P>
Lenin is one of the best known and the most influential figures
of the 20th century, the article says. Neither history nor the
people will forget Lenin, a great man who pushed forward the
advancement of the 20th century, it says.
</P>
<P>
Lenin devoted all his life to the cause of emancipating the
proletarians and working people worldwide and building socialism
and communism, making an indelible contribution to the progress
and development of the human society in the 20th century.
</P>
<P>
Lenin led the Bolsheviks and the Russian people to end the
military, feudalist and imperialist dictatorship in Russia through
three revolutions, especially the October Revolution in 1917, and
founded the world's first socialist country ruled by proletarians,
which found a new way to resolve three major contradictions, and
opened up a new era in human history to evolve from capitalism to
socialism.
</P>
<P>
Lenin created the basic system of socialism, creatively probed
the road for underdeveloped nations to adopt socialism, displayed
the bright prospects of socialism to the people of the whole world,
and thus pushed forward the rise and development of socialist
trends in the 20th century.
</P>
<P>
Lenin played an active role in the world's socialist movement,
helped establish and develop communist parties in different
countries, and supported and promoted the struggles for the
emancipation of people in countries under colonial rule.
</P>
<P>
Lenin combined Marxism with the international working class
movement and national liberation movement, as well as the reality
of the Russian revolution, which creatively utilized, enriched,
and developed Marxism.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000412.0147 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Magazine Publishes Article in Memory of Lenin (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The article calls Lenin the teacher of the proletarians of the
world and a sincere friend of the Chinese people, adding that he
closely observed the social changes in China and the development
of the Chinese revolution. Lenin pinned high hopes on the social
development in China and China's contributions to the world,
according to the article.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese people supported the Russian revolution in various
ways, and Lenin also considered the Chinese revolution to be
important and strategic.
</P>
<P>
The article denounces those who have denied Lenin's
achievements and Leninism, noting that the assessment of Lenin is
an assessment of the entire socialist cause in the 20th century.
Lenin made some mistakes, but so did some socialist countries
which encountered serious zigzags, and even tremendous changes and
breakups, which should be attributed to historic mistakes made by
those countries, not to Lenin.
</P>
<P>
Do not spill dirty water over Lenin, because denial of Lenin is
of course a denial of the entire history of Communists in the 20th
century, who fought boldly to found and build socialism.
</P>
<P>
Lenin's theory is a unique ideological and cultural system that
has been spread throughout the world and has cast profound impact
on the human spirit. According to UNESCO statistics, Lenin's works
once ranked first in the world in terms of circulation and
translated works.
</P>
<P>
The basic principles of Leninism, though a heritage from the
early 20th century, are guiding the current socialist construction
in China, and at the turn of this century, the Chinese people
still draw wisdom from Lenin's thought, especially in the
following aspects:
</P>
<P>
-- building a socialist economy;
</P>
<P>
-- developing a socialist democracy and legal system;
</P>
<P>
-- strengthening the socialist ruling party;
</P>
<P>
-- international relations and socialist foreign policies;
</P>
<P>
-- scientific methods of thinking.
</P>
<P>
The article makes the point that the most fundamental thing for
the Chinese Communists is to combine Marxism-Leninism with the
reality in China to consistently push forward the building of
socialism with China's own characteristics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
