<HEADLINE> American Scholar Expects Macao to Boost IT Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 12 (Xinhua) -- An American professor said at a
forum here Wednesday that Macao should boost the development of
its information technology to facilitate foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
To attract foreign investment with better infrastructure based
on information technology, the government should provide financial
assistance in building low-cost and fast access to the Internet,
according to Eduardo da Costa, a professor with Harvard University
of the United States.
</P>
<P>
Macao's advantage lies in the fact that phone bills are paid in
a fixed monthly sum and thus Internet surfers do not have to worry
much about the time they spend on the web, the professor said at
the Macao-Beijing International Business Forum which ended here
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The forum will reopen in Beijing on Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
