<HEADLINE> URGENT Chinese President Arrives in Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEL AVIV, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
arrived here Wednesday from Beijing for a week-long state visit to
Israel, at the invitation of his Israeli counterpart Ezer Weizman.
</P>
<P>
This is the first visit to Israel by a Chinese head of state
since the establishment of diplomatic ties between the two
countries in 1992.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Jiang is scheduled to hold talks with Weizman
and Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak to discuss ways of further
enhancing the bilateral ties and exchange views on the Middle East
peace process and other international issues of mutual concern.
</P>
<P>
Jiang will also meet with Knesset (parliament) Speaker Avraham
Burg and other Israeli government officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
