<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed mixed Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index rose 7.03
points to 940.60, the all-share Emas Index added 1.50 points to
246.58, the Industrial Index lost 4.19 points to 1,618.25 and the
Second Board Index shed 0.35 of a point to 280.50.
</P>
<P>
Losers led gainers by 371 to 344 while 150 counters were
unchanged and 96 untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's total turnover increased to 321.853 million shares
worth 1.082 billion ringgit (284.736 million U.S. dollars) from
305.540 million shares valued at 1.206 billion ringgit (317.368
million dollars) on Tuesday. 
</P>
