<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Meteorological Chief Warns of Floods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania may face floods
between now and the end of May if heavy rains continue, Mohamed
Mhita, director general of the Meteorological Department, has
warned.
</P>
<P>
Floods were likely to occur if more heavy rains pounded the
country in the next 50 days, he told the Guardian newspaper on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Mhita said the current rains in most parts of Tanzania would
continue up to the end of the next month. Though it will not fall
continuously, it is possible that some parts of the country will
have floods.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, such floods might not be similar to those
experienced throughout Tanzania in 1998 caused by the El-Nino
weather phenomenon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
