<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UEFA Postpones Decision on Leeds Semifinal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, April 12 (Xinhua) -- European soccer's governing body
UEFA has postponed a decision until Friday on whether Galatasaray
fans will be allowed to travel to Leeds at the second leg of the
UEFA Cup semifinal.
</P>
<P>
UEFA said in a statement on Wednesday that the delay was "to
allow UEFA to receive and fully evaluate written submissions from
both sides before making a decision".
</P>
<P>
Leeds asked UEFA to ban the Turkish club's fans from the second
leg at Elland Road in the wake of the knifing to death of two
Leeds fans in Istanbul before the first leg last week.
</P>
<P>
Leeds want the ban on away supporters because they are worried
about retaliation over the killings while Galatasaray have asked
UEFA to have the match played at a neutral ground if the security
of their fans cannot be guaranteed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
