<HEADLINE> Another E-venture Website Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 12 (Xinhua)-- Another website engaged in venture
capital investment opened today, adding further heat to the
Internet economy.
</P>
<P>
The website: http://www.e-ventures.com.cn/, is an extension of
traditional financial services, said its chairman Wang Boming.
Wang has played a key role in the success of Guangxi Yuchai in New
York in international capital raising for Huayuan, a Beijing-based
real estate developer, in addition to some fund management
experiences.
</P>
<P>
The new website will provide economic and financial information
and e-commerce products, carry out on-line trading in cooperation
with several banks, securities firms, and financial institutions.
</P>
<P>
The website's strategic partners include the South China
Morning Post, CITIC, and the China Securities Market Research and
Design Center.
</P>
<P>
Over 200 people from key government departments and colleges
and businesses attended the opening ceremony today.  
</P>
