<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Railway Transport Continues to Profit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 12 (Xinhua)-- China's railways system
transported 263 million people during the first quarter this year,
up 6.9 percent over the same period last year, said the Ministry
of Railways.
</P>
<P>
Cargo transport rose by 2.9 percent to 393 million tons.
</P>
<P>
The railways earned 26.81 billion yuan in profit, up 8.1
percent on an annual basis. This income includes 9.987 billion
yuan through ticket sales, up 15.9 percent, and cargo transport
income of 13.083 billion yuan, up 2 percent.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said the first quarter's performance "has made a
pleasing start toward the annual profit goal." 
</P>
</TEXT>
