<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Making Five-Year Plan for Natural Science Fund </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 12 (Xinhua) -- China has started to work on its
tenth five-year plan (2000-2005) and a long-term program to 2010
to improve funding for natural science and basic research programs,
according to Chen Jia'er, director of the State Natural Science
Fund Committee (SNSFC).
</P>
<P>
Chen, also a member of the Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS),
said priorities will be given to research fields in which China
has already gained a position in international academic circles.
The science foundation will also strengthen support to innovative
research subjects, Chen emphasized.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the natural science fund will make efforts to
promote inter-disciplinary studies.
</P>
<P>
Biotechnology, information science, China's water problem in
the 21st century, global change, agricultural sustainable
development, physics and other topics have been listed as
priorities for discussion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
