<HEADLINE> Mainland-HKSAR Intellectual Property Symposium Starts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 12 (Xinhua) -- The State Intellectual Property
Office (SIPO), together with the Intellectual Property Department
of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR), today
opened a high-profile symposium here today.
</P>
<P>
The Mainland-HKSAR Intellectual Property Symposium 2000 aims to
promote close links and further cooperation between the two sides
in this field, organizers said.
</P>
<P>
Dozens of intellectual property scholars from the two sides are
scheduled to deliver speeches at the three-day symposium,
discussing similarities and differences in their intellectual
property protection systems.
</P>
<P>
The proposed topics include protection of patents, industrial
designs, trademarks and copyright, commercialization and
evaluation of patents and designs, and intellectual property
public education.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Ying, commissioner of the SIPO, said that China will do
better in intellectual property protection in the coming new
century.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 intellectual property scholars and law experts
are taking part in the symposium.  
</P>
</TEXT>
