<HEADLINE> Australia's Servcorp Launches Business Center in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 12 (Xinhua) -- The Australia-based Servcorp,
the largest provider of serviced offices in Asia Pacific region,
announced today its presence in Hong Kong with a business center
in the prestigious Bank of China Tower.
</P>
<P>
This was the second business center Servcorp opened in China,
Marcus Moufarrige, general manager of the Asia Pacific head-office
in Hong Kong told a press conference this afternoon. Servcorp set
up its first China center in Pudong, Shanghai, just 18 months ago.
</P>
<P>
Servcorp has so far provided business center facilities and
virtual offices to over 30,000 clients ranging from multinational
organizations to small businesses in over 522 locations throughout
the world, according to Moufarrige.
</P>
<P>
Servcorp provides facilities to companies which are driven by
the continuing trend for outsourcing and technological
developments in areas such as networking and communications, the
general manager said.
</P>
<P>
"In a long run, Servcorp's business scope in China's mainland
is unlimited, but right now the operation in Hong Kong is more
profitable," Moufarrige said, adding that Servcorp will set up its
third business center in Beijing soon.
</P>
<P>
On the 25th floor of the Bank of China Tower, Servcorp has over
50 offices with top-level facilities and security in the state-of-
the-art building, boasting one of the best phone systems in China,
Moufarrige said.
</P>
<P>
Servcorp has plans for an even-growing number of similar
locations globally, staffed with multilingual teams and outfitted
to meet a variety of business needs including new market entry,
special projects, temporary office expansion, regional or branch
offices in high quality prime-positioned office sites, he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
