<HEADLINE> HK Stocks Close Higher on PCCW Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks closed higher
today as market sentiment was lifted by news of an alliance
between Australia's Telstra Corp. and Pacific Century Cyberworks (
PCCW).
</P>
<P>
The key Hang Seng index went up 89.43 points, or 0.54 percent,
to close at 16,577.09 on a turnover of 11.698 billion HK dollars (
1.500 billion U.S. dollars), compared with Tuesday's 9.477 billion
HK dollars (1.215 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Of the four sub-indices of HSI, Finance, Utilities and Commerce
&AMP; Industry registered a gain of 0.62 percent, 1.04 percent, and 0.
77 percent, respectively, while Properties lost 0.51 percent.
</P>
<P>
Hang Seng China Enterprises went down 0.50 percent and Hang
Seng China-Affiliated Corporations Index down 1.55 percent.
</P>
