<HEADLINE> Nawaz Sharif Files Appeal in SHC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's deposed prime
minister Nawaz Sharif Wednesday filed appeal in Sindh High Court (
SHC)challenging the Anti-Terrorism Court (ATC) verdict in the
plane conspiracy case.
</P>
<P>
The petition was filed by a leading criminal lawyer Azizullah
Sheikh, who was hired by Nawaz Sharif after the ATC judge
convicted him and acquitted six co-accused on April 6.
</P>
<P>
The lawyer handed over the appeal to the deputy registrar of
the SHC, Ali Mohammed, who said a date for a preliminary hearing
would be fixed after scrutiny of the documents.
</P>
<P>
Nawaz Sharif was sentenced on April 6 to life imprisonment on
charge of refusing to let a passenger plane land in Karachi
endangering the lives of some 200 people on board.
</P>
<P>
In a verdict handed down by Anti-Terrorism Court No. One in the
southern Pakistani city of Karachi, Sharif was found guilty of
hijacking and terrorism. However, he was acquitted of attempted
murder and kidnapping.
</P>
<P>
The court also ordered a fine of 500,000 rupees (9,615 U.S.
dollars) for each charge and the confiscation of all his
properties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
