<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Tamil Rebels Sink Navy Patrol Craft </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's Tamil rebels
Wednesday sank a navy craft, killing one sailor and injuring three
others,a military spokesman said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The craft sank at Kalpitiya port in the north western Sri Lanka
after a fighting with a boat of Tamil rebels. During the
confrontation the rebel boat was destroyed with a big explosion,
spokesman Rp Witana said.
</P>
<P>
"The navy patrol craft was heavily damaged due to the explosion
of the rebel boat and sank subsequently," Witana said.
</P>
<P>
The attack on the navy craft came as fighting raged in the
northern Jaffna Peninsula when government troops tried to clear an
area between Muhamalai and Pallai recaptured on Monday from the
rebels who are fighting against the government for a separate
Tamil state in the north and east of the country.
</P>
<P>
At least 11 government soldiers were killed and another 190
were wounded in Monday's clashes along a strategic highway in the
Jaffna Peninsula. The rebel casualties were reportedly also very
high. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
