<HEADLINE> Thailand's New Cabinet Members Sworn in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 12 (Xinhua) -- The six new members of the Thai
cabinet were sworn in to office after being led by Prime Minister
Chuan Leekpai to an audience with King Bhumibol Adulyadej
Wednesday afternoon at Klai Kangwon Palace in the coastal city of
Hua Hin, some 200 kilometers southwest of Bangkok, an informed
source told Xinhua.
