resign from posts in private companies if they hold any.
</P>
<P>
The Thai cabinet underwent a minor reshuffle Tuesday, which was
the third after the current government took office in November
1997.
</P>
<P>
The six-party ruling coalition, holding a comfortable majority
of 237 in the 385-member lower house of parliament, is expected to
call a general election before November this year when its term
expires. 
