<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shares Finish Slightly Higher on S'pore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Share prices closed slightly
firmer on Singapore Stock Market Wednesday, with the benchmark
Straits Times Index up 4.01 points to end at 2,135.39 points.
</P>
<P>
The total volume was 212.17 million shares worth 288.03 million
Singapore dollars (about 168.44 million U.S. dollars). There were
85 losers against 163 gainers with 282 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
AirOcean topped the actives chart with 105.31 million counters
changing hands. It was followed by JurTech which had 18.64 million
shares done. Fastech was the next registering a turnover of 16.57
million units.
</P>
<P>
PacCent led gainers of the day gaining 170 cents to close at 16.
60 Singapore dollars. Creative 50 moved up 120 cents to finish at
48.70 Singapore dollars. SPH 100 ended 80 cents higher at 31.50
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Seaview was the biggest loser of the day sliding down 40 cents
to close at 8.20 Singapore dollars. Chartered and NatElec each
sank 30 cents to finish at 13.40 and 10.40 Singapore dollars,
respectively. DataCrft lose 25 cents to end at 7.95 Singapore
dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
