<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nigeria Grants Citizenship to Foreigners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABUJA, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria has awarded citizenship to
43 foreigners in order to help accelerate the country's
technological and economic development.
</P>
<P>
At a ceremony in the Nigerian capital on Tuesday, Vice
President Atiku Abubakar said on behalf of President Olusegun
Obasanjo the beneficiaries were expected to use their "contact and
exposure" to assist the country's technological development "with
a view to making Nigeria great and a pride to all".
</P>
<P>
Recipients of the award, the first since 1994, included 26
Lebanese, four Chinese, one British and one from Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
Abubakar told recipients who had stayed a minimum of 15 years
in the country: "You have joined the Nigerian family and should
use your energy for the development of a virile and
self-sustaining economy."
</P>
<P>
Speaking for the recipients, Anthony Gill, chairman of the
Lagos-based metal box company, said their applications for
citizenship showed their confidence in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
