<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Latvian Prime Minister Resigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Latvian Prime Minister Andris
Skele on Wednesday announced resignation just nine months after
the current center-right coalition government was formed.
</P>
<P>
According to the Interfax news agency, Skele is to submit his
letter of resignation to President Vaira Vike-Freiberga, who will
name a successor. Vike-Freiberga has not made any comments on the
situation, however.
</P>
<P>
The Fatherland and Freedom nationalist bloc, which is
represented in the ruling coalition, stated earlier that Skele can
no longer head the government.
</P>
<P>
The Skele government was formed on July 16, 1999 and was
Latvia's eighth cabinet since Latvia regained independence in the
early 1990s. 
</P>
</TEXT>
