<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Oman Denies Signing Defense Agreement With Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Omani Foreign Ministry denied
that it had signed a defense agreement with Iran, terming reports
about such an agreement as "groundless," a newspaper of the United
Arab Emirates reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Abu Dhabi-based "Itihad" quoted an official of the ministry
as saying that "the mission of the Omani military delegation, which
has just ended its visit to Tehran, was only within the technical
context."
</P>
<P>
Commander of Omani Air Force Mohamed Bin Mahfouz has just
returned from a five-day visit to Iran, during which he held talks
with his Iranian counterpart with a view to improve military
relations between the two countries, the official said, noting that
Mahfouz did not sign any defense accords during the visit.
</P>
<P>
Oman and Iran signed an accord for military cooperation in
November 1998, following the improvement in relations between Iran
and the Gulf states. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
