<HEADLINE> China's First Software Institute to Be Built in Northeast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, April 12 (Xinhua) -- A software institute planned for
northwest China will be the first of its kind in the country.
</P>
<P>
The Dalian Software Park is working in cooperation with NEU-
Alpine, a leading Chinese software firm, to create an info-
engineering institute in Dalian.
</P>
<P>
The software park will offering management training and
software development, and aims to establish an IT talent pool in
northeast China to train qualified professionals who can meet the
demands of both domestic and foreign enterprises.
</P>
<P>
