<HEADLINE> San Antonio Spurs Beats Sacramento Kings 98-92 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 11 (Xinhua) -- David Robinson scored six of
his 26 points in overtime and also grabbed 15 rebounds as the San
Antonio Spurs beat the Sacramento Kings 98-92.
</P>
<P>
Tim Duncan had 18 points and 13 rebounds for the Spurs, who
outscored Sacramento 14-8 in overtime Tuesday night to win their
third straight game and reach the 50-win mark for the fifth time
in seven seasons.
</P>
<P>
In Dallas, Mavericks defeated Portland Trail Blazers 92-81.
Michael Finley scored 24 points and Dirk Nowitzki added 21 points
and 14 rebounds as the Dallas Mavericks won their fifth straight
game.
</P>
<P>
Rasheed Wallace's 13 points paced the Trail Blazers, who shot
34.6 percent from the field (28-for-81) and hit only 19 of 33 free
throws.
</P>
<P>
In Chicago, Bulls edged New Jersey Nets 100-93. Elton Brand led
Chicago with 22 points, 15 rebounds and a career-high seven
assists and Matt Maloney was 5-of-6 from 3-point range for a
season-high 19 points as the Bulls overpowered New Jersey.
</P>
<P>
The Bulls made a season-high 11 3-pointers and shot over 50
percent at home for the first time this season. Keith Van Horn led
the Nets with 25 points.
</P>
<P>
In Denver, Houston Rockets eliminated Nuggets 103-93. Walt
Williams had 23 points and 12 rebounds and the Rockets outscored
the Nuggets 14-2 in the final 6:20 to win their fourth straight
game.
</P>
<P>
Nick Van Exel led the Nuggets with 27 points and 11 assists.
Raef LaFrentz scored 16 points for Denver.
</P>
<P>
In Los Angeles, Phoenix Suns routed Clippers 95-88. Cliff
Robinson scored 22 points and Todd Day got 10 of his 18 points in
the fourth quarter as the Suns dealt the Clippers their 13th
consecutive defeat.
</P>
<P>
With their 11th win in 15 contests, the Suns reached the 50-win
plateau for the ninth time in 12 seasons and the 13th time in club
history. Rookie Lamar Odom had 26 points and a career-high 15
rebounds for the Clippers.
</P>
<P>
In Oakland, California, Golden State Warriors beat Vancouver
Grizzlies 109-97. Larry Hughes scored 28 points and Jason Caffey
and Mark Davis each added 25.
</P>
<P>
Adonal Foyle added 15 points for the Warriors, who won
consecutive games for the first time since late February. Michael
Dickerson collected 24 points to lead Vancouver. 
</P>
</TEXT>
