<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Precipitation Expected for Parts of China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Some parts of China are expected
to experience precipitation in the next three days, China's
Central Meteorological Observatory said today.
</P>
<P>
The Observatory said much of China to the south of the Yangtze
River will have rainfall ranging from five to 20 mm.
</P>
<P>
Rainfalls of 30-50 mm are forecast for east and south part of
Guizhou Province, parts of south China's Guangdong Province and
Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region and areas between the Yangtze
River and Nanling Mountains. Rainfalls of 80 to 150 mm are also
forecast for isolated areas with occasional strong winds and
thunder storms.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, rainfalls or snowfalls ranging from two to eight mm
are expected from April 12-14 in winter wheat-growing areas in
northern China, such as the eastern part of northwest China,
central and southern parts of north China, regions between the
Yangtze and Yellow rivers, the Hanshui River Basin and areas
between the Yangtze and Huaihe rivers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
