<HEADLINE> Nepal-China Forum to Be Held in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, April 12 (Xinhua) -- The fourth meeting of Nepal-
China Non-governmental Cooperation Forum is going to be held at
the end of October this year in Beijing, China, President of
Nepalese Chambers of Commerce and Industry(FNCCI) Pradeep Shrestha
told Xinhua Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is aimed at strengthening the non-governmental
cooperation between the business communities of Nepal and China,
especially at attracting more Chinese investment in Nepal, he said.
</P>
<P>
One particular agenda of the meeting will be exploring the
potentialities to set up more Nepal-China joint ventures in Nepal,
he added.
</P>
<P>
Shrestha stressed that the establishment of the forum has
significantly contributed to enhancing the economic and commercial
information exchange between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The forum, established in 1996, holds its annual meeting in
Nepal and China in turn to discuss issues relating to cooperations
and exchanges on trade, investment and tourism between private
sectors of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
FNCCI is an umbrella organization of the Nepalese private
sector and plays a key role in promoting business and industry in
the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
