<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Congolese Refugees Enter Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 12 (Xinhua) -- About 221 refugees fleeing the
conflict in the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) have
entered Zambia since last Wednesday, United Nations High
Commission for Refugees (UNHCR) has revealed.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman for the UNHCR Dominik Bartsch confirmed here on
Tuesday that an arrival of 50 refugees was being recorded every
day, Zambia Daily Mail reported on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted the spokesman as saying that most of the
refugees crossing into the country were hunger stricken.
</P>
<P>
Bartsch attributed the increase of refugees in Zambia's
Northern and Luapula Provinces to fighting in the DRC, saying: "We
are sending our team to go and verify the situation on the
ground."
</P>
<P>
About 19,600 Congolese refugees were at Mwange in Northern
Province, but the number of refugees at Mwange would rise to
25,000 soon, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
