<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Not to Hold National Independence Celebrations This year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe will not traditionally
hold national celebrations this year to mark the 20th anniversary
of its independence, Minister of Information, Posts and
Telecommunications Chen Chimutengwende has said.
</P>
<P>
However, he said President Robert Mugabe will address the
nation on state television on Independence Day which falls on
April 18.
</P>
<P>
The minister said on Tuesday the money that had been set aside
for the national celebrations will be used to assist the victims
of Cyclone Eline.
</P>
<P>
The devastating floods caused by Cyclone Eline which ravaged
Zimbabwe last month left 100 people dead and more than 200,000
homeless and inflicted damages worth over 55 million U.S. dollars.
 
