<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe's Parliament Approves World Bank Loan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwean Parliament has approved
a five million U.S. dollar loan from the World Bank for the
inception phase of the second stage of resettlement program, which
seeks to redistribute five million hectares of land to 118,800
families.
</P>
<P>
Imploring the House to ratify the loan, Minister of Finance
Herbert Murerwa said on Tuesday that land reform was one of the
important challenges facing Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
"The enormous inequality of access to land threatens the social
and political stability of the country," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Some 4,500 white farmers in the large scale commercial farming
sector own 11.2 million hectares of generally high quality land,
while around one million households, over five million people,
live on 16.4 million hectares of generally poor quality land," he
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
