<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Serena Williams Retired at WTA Tour Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Hobbling on an injured knee,
second-seeded Serena Williams of the United States left the WTA
Tour tennis tournament held in Amelia Island of Florida just the
way her sister did last year.
</P>
<P>
Williams retired Tuesday after falling behind Paola Suarez of
Argentina 3-6, 6-4, 2-5.
</P>
<P>
Williams was hampered by an injured right knee in February, but
has played three tournaments since and made the round of 16 or
better in all of them.
</P>
<P>
Her loss to Suarez, the 62nd-ranked player in the world, was
similar to the way Venus Williams exited this tournament last year.
Venus lost her first match to 140th-ranked Sonya Jeyaseelan.
</P>
<P>
Other winners included fourth-seeded Conchita Martinez of Spain,
who outclassed Russian Elena Dementieva 7-5, 6-2; No. 7 Russian
Anna Kournikova, who edged Anne Kremer of Luxembourg 7-5, 7-6 (7-4)
; No. 8 Barbara Schett of Austria, who defeated Gala Leon Garcia
of Spain 6-2, 6-2; and No. 10 South African Amanda Coetzer, who
routed Russian Tatiana Panova 6-0, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Top-seeded Mary Pierce and defending champion Monica Seles will
play their first matches on Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
