<HEADLINE> Abandoned Baby White-Cheeked Gibbon Bred in Zoo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, April 12 (Xinhua) -- A two-month old white-cheeked
gibbon abandoned by her mother at birth has been raised by the
Nanning Municipal Zoo in southwest China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The female gibbon, Xiao Ye ("Little Wild") was abandoned by her
mother because she did not have enough breast milk to feed her.
Zookeepers were concerned whether they could feed the baby gibbon
without her mother.
</P>
<P>
The white-cheeked gibbon is high on the list of the country's
endangered animals. The Zoo has set up an artificial insemination
program to help improve reproduction among white-cheeked gibbons.
</P>
</TEXT>
