<HEADLINE> East China Province Benefits From Foreign Expertise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, April 12 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangxi Province
has witnessed rapid increase in its economic returns through
introduction of foreign talent and expertise.
</P>
<P>
According to the provincial science and technology committee,
Jiangxi province has introduced from overseas 113 foreign new
technologies and improved agriculture, forestry, grass planting,
animal husbandry and aquatic production in recent years, and this
has helped increase its annual direct economic returns by 20
million yuan (2.4 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The province plans to introduce 10 foreign agricultural
technologies and new grain varieties, in addition to 120 programs
concerning foreign experts and professionals.
</P>
<P>
Feifei, director of the province's office for importing foreign
expertise, said that the aim of the introduction of foreign
technologies and improved grain varieties is to help increase
agricultural production efficiency and raise the income of farmers.
</P>
</TEXT>
