<HEADLINE> Internet Helps Handicapped </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Liu Zhibang, an eleven-year-old
boy from Dalian in northeast China's Liaoning Province, has got a
computer and a few books donated from a Dalian-based company,
thanks to the help of www.aixin.com.cn.
</P>
<P>
The website officially opened on December 3 last year by Sun
Shuiming, a handicapped man also from Dalian to inspire
handicapped people and provide information on Red Cross offices
and volunteer societies around China.
</P>
<P>
Liu has suffered from epilepsy since he was six years old. No
hospital has been able to diagnose his illness.
</P>
<P>
" I just want to build up a bridge between the handicapped and
the normal and develop mutual understanding," said Liu. He has
told his story to others and provided a needed support system for
many handicapped people.
</P>
<P>
So far, over 3,000 people have browsed this website. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
