<HEADLINE> Guangdong Expands Agricultural Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Guangdong now exports 30
percent of its agricultural goods to 170 countries and regions,
and the volume of agricultural products purchased for export was
three billion yuan a year.
</P>
<P>
Local agricultural officials attributed the success to
attracting foreign technology and management expertise in
agriculture.
</P>
<P>
In the past two decades, Guangzhou has used over three billion
U.S. dollars of overseas investment in the agricultural sector,
and 1,500 joint-ventures have been established.
</P>
<P>
More than 2,000 agricultural export production and processing
bases have been built in the province. 
</P>
