<HEADLINE> Kwan Beats Slutskaya in Figurre Skating Challenge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 11 (Xinhua) -- American Michelle Kwan, the
three-time world champion, earned a perfect 6.0 for presentation
en route to a victory over world silver medalist Russian Irina
Slutskaya at the 2000 International Figure Skating Challenge in
Binghamton, New York on Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
Kwan defeated Slutskaya in their first meeting since she won
the gold medal over the Russian skater at worlds in Nice, France.
</P>
<P>
Both Kwan and Slutskaya received one 6.0 for presentation, but
Kwan collected straight 5.9s for technique to win the 1-on-1
battle.
</P>
<P>
Despite Kwan's performance, the United States team couldn't
overcome a strong showing by the International Team in the final
ISU-sanctioned open event of the 1999-2000 season.
</P>
<P>
Canadian Elvis Stojko's win over two-time U.S. champion Michael
Weiss clinched the overall victory for the International Team.
</P>
<P>
The only other U.S. victory was 1992 Olympic gold medalist
Kristi Yamaguchi over two-time Olympic gold medalist German
Katarina Witt.
</P>
<P>
Another 1992 Olympic gold medalist, Victor Petrenko of the
Ukraine, opened the event with a close victory over five-time U.S.
champion Todd Eldredge.
</P>
<P>
Surya Bonaly of France, a three-time world silver medalist,
defeated current U.S. bronze medalist Sarah Hughes after Hughes
slipped on some footwork late in her program.
</P>
<P>
Russian and European champion Yevgeny Pluschenko defeated U.S.
silver medalist Timothy Goebel in the third men's matchup.
</P>
</TEXT>
