<HEADLINE> Foreign Consulates Comment on Guangzhou's Urban Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Foreign government officials
and consuls-general of foreign consulates from 13 countries in
Guangzhou convened together Monday to discuss urban construction
and environment protection in the city.
</P>
<P>
The Dutch consul-general Roos in Guangzhou complained of
traffic problems to the city Mayor Lin Shusen last year. "Since
the beginning of the year, I found that traveling around the city
had been much more convenient than before, and driving in the city
is an interesting thing."
</P>
<P>
"Since I came to Guangzhou three years ago, I have seen great
changes here, which is appealing to overseas investors," said Luis
T Cruz, the Philippine consul-general.
</P>
<P>
Stephen Lillie, the newly-arrived British consul-general in
Guangzhou, said that after the Britain Insurance Corp. is to open
business in Guangzhou in a few months, some British companies will
seek opportunities to develop subway construction in the city.
</P>
<P>
Consuls-general from Malaysia, Australia and Britain all are
willing to promote and develop friendly relations with Guangzhou.
