<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Soybean Action Plan In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 12 (Xinhua) -- The "soybean action plan",
designed to improve school children nutrition by drinking soybean
milk, has officially been launched in China, according to a report
in the "People's Daily".
</P>
<P>
The central government is expected to invest 100 million yuan (
about 12 million U.S. dollars) this year in promoting the program
in three provinces in northeastern China. In the next few years,
the program will be introduced to other parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
Official surveys showed that malnutrition is a major health
problem for children in China, especially those in underdeveloped
regions.
</P>
<P>
In some parts of the country, the average height of children
aged between 6 to 15 years are 3.3 to six centimeters lower than
the standard, while average weight is 1.8 to 2.5 kilograms below
standard. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000412.0272 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-12 </DATE_TIME>
