OPEC) will review the effects of the oil output increase decided
by the organization in March.
</P>
<P>
The OPEC ministers will hold an extraordinary meeting on June
21 in Vienna "to make a balance of the decisions taken in relation
to production, and the market will be analyzed to know its
performance," said Rodriguez in a communique of the Venezuelan
