<HEADLINE> Nepal Welcomes Summit of Two Korean sides in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, April 12 (Xinhua) -- The Nepali government welcomed
the first summit meeting to be held between the leaders of the
Republic of Korea and the Democratic People's Republic of Korea in
Pyongyang in June.
</P>
<P>
A press release issued by the Nepali Ministry of Foreign
Affairs, available Wednesday, said this is a significant and
positive development in inter-Korean relations.
</P>
<P>
Nepal hoped that the summit meeting will contribute to the
reunification process including peace and stability in the Korean
Peninsula.
</P>
<P>
The summit slated for June 12-14 is aimed at building
confidence and ending long-standing animosity between the northern
and southern sides of the Korean Peninsula.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will mainly discuss economic cooperation,
reconciliation and the reunion of families. It will also cover the
establishment of a regular channel of dialogue between the two
sides. 
</P>
