<HEADLINE> Number of Undernourished People Goes Down: FAO </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, April 11 (Xinhua) -- The number of people
undernourished in the world goes down by a little over 40 million
during the last three years, according to an FAO study.
</P>
<P>
The study, released Tuesday in Merida, Yucatan, southeastern
Mexico, said that until 1996 there were 800 million undernourished
in the developing countries and in countries with transition
economies.
</P>
<P>
"The rhythm of progress hasn't been enough to reach the
objective of 400 million with undernourishment for year 2015,"
said the report.
</P>
<P>
If the current tendency keeps on, if the number of
undernourished people goes down around eight million per year, the
total in 2015 would be 638 million, it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
