<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's exports of electronic
products surged 69 percent to 590 million U.S. dollars during the
first two months this year, compared to the same period last year,
said Brazil's Electronic and Electrical Industry Association
Tuesday.
