<HEADLINE> Regulations Drafted For Protecting Chinese Famous Tea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Regulations have been drafted
for protecting the production base of Longjing tea (Dragon Well
tea), a famous green tea produced in Hangzhou, capital of east
China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
The West Lake Longjing tea boasts a history of over 1,000 years
and is often called the "Empress of Green tea". The increase fake
Longjing tea products has caused all kinds of problems for
producing the tea.
</P>
<P>
According to the regulation, an area covering 168 square
kilometers has been designated for Longjing tea plantation.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
