<DOCNO> XIE20000412.0310 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-Italian Bus Sets Mileage Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, April 12 (Xinhua) -- A Sino-Italian mini-van has run 800,
000 kilometers without overhauls in China, setting a new record in
China's light-duty bus industry.
</P>
<P>
The mini-van, IVECO, is made by Nanjing Yuejin Group
Corporation and the Italian Fiat Group.
</P>
<P>
The driver of the van, Wu Guoqing, attributed the record to the
excellent quality and his care of the vehicle. Wu was awarded a
motor engine and a tourist ticket in ten European countries by the
producer.
</P>
<P>
Wu bought another IVECO two years ago, which has run more than
700,000 kilometers. Wu said that he is confident that the bus can
run one million kilometers without overhauls, the world's mileage
record for IVECOs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
