<HEADLINE> Chinese President Leaves for Five-Nation Trip </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
left here this morning by a special plane to kick off his state
visit to Israel, Palestine, Turkey, Greece and South Africa.
</P>
<P>
Jiang is on the visit at the invitation of President Ezer
Weizman of the State of Israel, President Yasser Arafat of the
State of Palestine, President Suleyman Demirel of the Republic of
Turkey, President Costis Stephanopoulos of the Republic of Greece,
and President Thabo Mbeki of the Republic of South Africa.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Jiang will go to Alexandria, Egypt, to meet
with President Muhammed Hosni Mubarak of the Arab Republic of
Egypt at Mubarak's invitation.
</P>
<P>
Those who saw Jiang and his delegation off at the Great Hall of
the People included Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji, Vice President Hu
Jintao, National People's Congress Standing Committee Vice-
Chairman Tian Jiyun, Central Military Commission Vice Chairman
Zhang Wannian, Member of the Secretariat of the Central Committee
of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Zeng Qinghong, Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference National Committee Vice
Chairman Wan Guoquan, Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan, Minister in
charge of Central Foreign Affairs Office Liu Huaqiu, and Deputy
Director of the General Office of CPC Central Committee Bai Keming,
as well as diplomatic envoys from the above-mentioned six
countries.
</P>
<P>
Accompanying Jiang on the visit are Jiang's wife Wang Yeping,
Vice Premier Qian Qichen and his wife Zhou Hanqiong, State
Councilor Wu Yi, Director of the General Office of CPC Central
Committee Wang Gang, Minister in charge of the State Development
Planning Commission Zeng Peiyan, Director of the Policy Research
Office of CPC Central Committee Teng Wensheng, Vice Foreign
Minister Ji Peiding, Deputy Director of the General Office of CPC
Central Committee and Director of the Central Guards Bureau You
Xigui, Vice Minister of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation Sun
Guangxiang, Special Assistant Wang Huning and Director of
President Jiang's Office Jia Ting'an.  
</P>
</TEXT>
