<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Foreign Exchange Reserves Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's net foreign exchange
reserves increased by 121.2 million U.S. dollars to 18.63 billion
U.S. dollars in the week ending on April 7.
</P>
<P>
The rise was the result of an increase in oil revenues,
according to a press release issued by the central bank, Bank
Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
Gross foreign exchange reserves, which are net reserves plus
outstanding foreign exchange contracts, also increased by 119.9
million dollars to 29.85 billion dollar, the press release was
quoted by the Antara News Agency Wednesday as saying. 
</P>
</TEXT>
