<HEADLINE> Xinhua International News Summary at 0100 GMT, April 12 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA -- Peru's presidential candidate Alberto Fujimori has
obtained up to now 49.53 percent of votes in Sunday' s general
elections, National Electoral Processes Organization (NEPO) said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
NEPO specified second place is being occupied by candidate of
political grouping "Peru Possible", Alejandro Toledo, with 38.91
percent of votes. (Peru-Election)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- Russian President Vladimir Putin will make an
official visit to the United Kingdom on coming Sunday, a spokesman
for Downing Street said.
</P>
<P>
Putin is expected to fly into London late on Sunday night for
talks with Prime Minister Tony Blair.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman also confirmed that Britain was "still under
active discussion" with Russia on a possible meeting between
Putin and Queen Elizabeth II. Russia-UK-Putin-Visit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak won the support
for a planned Israeli troop pull-out of southern Lebanon from the
Clinton administration when he held talks with the U.S. Secretary
of State on Tuesday, but he was also pressed to move fast on the
Israeli-Palestinian track in the Middle east peace process.
</P>
<P>
Albright praised Barak at a news conference for planning to
pull Israeli troops out of southern Lebanon in July under U.N.
resolutions. (US-Israel-Pullback)
</P>
<P>
