<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jobless Rate Rises to Nearly 53 Percent in Nicaragua </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, April 11 (Xinhua) -- The jobless rate continued to
rise in Nicaragua, with the figure up to 52.5 percent from 48.1
percent in September, 1999, the Nicaraguan Studies Institute (NSI)
said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
During the period from September to the present, it said, 52.5
percent of the country's working force failed to find permanent
jobs.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the number of employed people decreased from 51.9
percent in September 1999 to the present 47.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
Unemployment in the urban areas reached 52.6 percent, which is
much higher than 43.8 percent for the rural areas, the institute
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
