<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Quick Response Smoothes Beijing's Traffic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 12 (Xinhua) -- The quick response method adopted
by traffic police has helped to smooth traffic in this capital
city, famous for its slow traffic over the past few years.
</P>
<P>
To change the situation, the municipal traffic administration
bureau last year adopted the drastic reform of quick response.
</P>
<P>
This method demands that police arrive at the scene in less
than four minutes after receiving a call and complete their work
in an average of five minutes.
</P>
<P>
Over the past year, 43,559 accidents were handled with the
method, greatly reducing the traffic jams in the city, which now
has over 1.5 million motor vehicles.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that 80 percent of the traffic
accidents in Beijing are minor ones.
</P>
<P>
Before this new method, the city's traffic police usually took
an average of 30 minutes to deal with a single minor incident.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
