<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Returned Olympic Diver Fu Mingxia Heads into Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Three-time Olympic champion Fu
Mingxia held off a strong challenge from her synchronized pair Guo
Jingjing to advance into the women's three-meter springboard final
at the Chinese national diving championships here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Led through preliminary, Fu gathered 587.60 points, while her
nearest rival Guo, who suffered a big mistake in the morning,
surged back in the semifinal and snatched the second place in 555.
85.
</P>
<P>
"I just performed OK today. I hope I can do better in the final,
" said the 22-year-old Fu, who now studies in prestigious Qinghua
University in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The nine-day diving event was introduced in the same schedule
as what will be used at Sydney Olympic Games. Wednesday will see
the finals of women's three-meter springboard, synchro platform
and men's three-meter synchro springboard. 
</P>
</TEXT>
