<HEADLINE> Britain Seeded for Davis Cup World Group Draw </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Britain are one of eight seeded
nations in Wednesday's qualifying draw for the Davis Cup world
group.
</P>
<P>
France, Italy, Morroco, Switzerland, Sweden, the Netherlands
and Zimbabwe are also seeded and will all be kept apart.
</P>
<P>
Austria, Belarus, Belgium, Chile, Ecuador, India, Romania and
Uzbekistan are the unseeded countries in the draw.
</P>
<P>
The winning nations in the qualifying round to be played in
July will secure places in the 2001 Davis Cup world group, while
the losers will compete in the zonal group one competitions.
</P>
