<P>
Justice Department spokesman Myron Marlin said that Reno is
planning to work out a resolution, trying to meet with the parties
concerned to seek a cooperative settlement in this case.
</P>
<P>
Marlin said Reno would meet with the Miami relatives who is
taking care of Elian and community leaders in Miami, where angry
Cuban exiles have vowed to prevent the boy's return to his father,
Juan Miguel Gonzalez.
</P>
<P>
Earlier Wednesday, the father indicated in a meeting with the
Rev. Joan Brown Campbell that he was through with negotiating and
is going to simply ask now that the attorney general issue a court
order and that the boy be returned immediately to him.
</P>
