<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Maria Minna, Canada's Minister for
International Cooperation, announced an additional 1.5 million
Canadian dollars (about 1 million U.S. dollars) in emergency aid
to drought-stricken Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
Canada's new contribution has brought the country's assistance
to Ethiopia since April 5 to 7.75 million dollars (about 5.35
million U.S. dollars), which are being delivered through the
Canadian International Development Agency (CIDA).
