children, will starve to death unless there is a rapid deployment
of the food, water and emergency resources," said the minister.
</P>
<P>
Poor rainfall over the past three years has caused drought,
crop failures and the disappearance of grazing land in many areas
of Ethiopia, where recurring drought has plagued more than 80
percent of its 60 million people over the past three decades.
