<HEADLINE> Uganda Spends 20 Million U.S. Dollars on Barrack Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Uganda has spent over 20 million
U.S. dollars on construction of barracks since 1986 when the
National Resistance Movement came to power, a senior official said
on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
State Minister for Defense Steven Kavuma told a parliamentary
committee on security and defense that the expenditure on barrack
construction has accounted for some 60 percent of the total sum
his ministry has spent over the past 14 years.
</P>
<P>
Responding to queries about the accountability of the fund, the
minister said that the auditor-general has appointed a team to
audit the related spending and would come up with a final report
on that.
</P>
<P>
Uganda's defense budget accounts for roughly two percent of the
country' s gross domestic product over the past few years. Quite a
few bilateral and multilateral donors have let out a loud outcry
for reduction of this budget. 
</P>
