<DOCNO> XIE20000412.0363 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Technology Stocks Tumble In Third Straight Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 12 (Xinhua) -- The technology stocks on Wall
Street tumbled Wednesday in the third straight session, dragging
the technology heavy Nasdaq composite index below the 4,000
milestone.
</P>
<P>
At the close of session, the Nasdaq index fell 286.27 or 7.1
percent at 3,769.63, adding to the losses of 132.30 points Tuesday
and 258.25 points Monday.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were also lower. The Dow Jones
industrial average fell 161.95 at 11,125.13 and the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 index fell 33.42 at 1,467.17.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq plunged after Goldman Sachs analyst Rick Sherlund
cut his revenue estimate for Microsoft to 5.75 billion U.S.
dollars from 5.95 billion dollars in the last quarter. The revised
estimate gave a heavy blew to the broad tech market. Dell, IBM and
Hewlett-Packard as well as Microsoft were sharply lower.
</P>
<P>
The composite fell today after hitting the record closing high
of 5,048.62 points on March 10 and eliminated all the gains this
year. The index is now down more than 4 percent in the year to
date.
</P>
<P>
Rules against Microsoft in an antitrust case early last week
sparked a big selloff for Microsoft and other technology stocks.
The Nasdaq composite fell 349.15 points on April 3 and 574.57
points in the session on the following day.
</P>
<P>
The Dow index trended downward in the late session from the
positive territory as investors sell blue chips to raise cash in
case the Nasdaq's fall triggers a new round of margin calls from
investment brokerages to cover up stocks on margin buying.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index fell 6.95 at 654.25 and the American Stock
Exchange index fell 18.06 at 926.79. The Russell 2000 index of
smaller companies fell 16.69 at 493.44.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 10-to-9 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,527 up, 1,480 down and 451
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume increased to 1.14 billion shares from 967.16
million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
