<HEADLINE> London And Paris Markets Fall at Close as New Tech Retreat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 12 (Xinhua) - London and Paris markets fell at
close Wednesday as Technology and media stocks were undermined by
further losses in the closely -watched US Nasdaq index.
</P>
<P>
London's FTSE 100 index, the benchmark for Europe's biggest
stock market, fell 0.5 percent to 6350.8, after being up as much
as 1 percent in morning trading.
</P>
<P>
The biggest decliner was British Sky Broadcasting, which fell 6.
5 percent, while the world's second-largest advertising company,
WPP, fell 6.3 percent. Media company Pearson fell 5 percent.
</P>
<P>
Computer software companies didn't fair any better. Logica fell
5.5 percent and accounting software group Sage slipped 6.2 percent,
while chip maker ARM Holdings fell 4.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
However, the FTSE Eurotop 300, an index of Europe's biggest
companies, rose 0.3 percent, with its transport, food and drug sub-
indexes climbing more than 1 percent.
</P>
<P>
The blue-chip CAC 40 in Paris, a leading gainer in recent
sessions, fell 33.89 points, or 0.54 percent, to 6227.53, after
advancing as much as 1 percent earlier.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, the Xetra Dax was barely changed, up just 0.41
point, or 0.01 percent, at 7443.07. 
</P>
</TEXT>
